modules.description: Constructs date and time values with precise control over calendar components, time zones, and offset adjustments, supporting partial or full specification of year, month, day, hour, minute, second, and nanoseconds. Operates on integers, weekdays, time zones, and time spans, with strict validation based on provided parameters. Used to create structured timestamps for logging, scheduling, or time-based data processing where exact temporal alignment is critical.

Flattens sequences or lists of integer or weekday ranges into continuous sequences, handling month, ISO week, and day ranges. Works with range types represented as tuples and sequences or lists. Used to generate expanded date or time unit lists from interval data.

Handles date and time parsing, formatting, and arithmetic using custom date and time types. Supports timezone conversions and duration calculations. Enables precise manipulation of calendar dates and clock times for scheduling and logging tasks.

Encapsulates date and time construction with precise control over components and time zones, while enabling the expansion of range-based data into continuous sequences. Supports operations on integers, weekdays, and time spans, with strict validation and flexible specification. Can generate detailed timestamps for precise scheduling or transform interval data into expanded date lists. Enables tasks like creating exact event times or generating full calendar ranges from partial definitions.
